10.19.21  6:39 pm   what's the chord on "supposed to be" in your new song, relative to the key that section's in (so like ii minor instead of G minor)

      that's Gmaj7 over A. we were in the key of F before, and soon will be in D. this chord is the first sign that we're breaking out of the key. technically this chord fits into the key of D, but that hasn't been revealed yet at that moment, so it doesn't quite count yet as the key of D. it's in limbo at that point

10.19.21  4:55 pm   Why are almost all of your answers shorter than their respective questions

      it's my instincitve tendency to give long long long long answers. i used to do that, then i realized that's probably pretty gross, so i turned over a new leaf and started trimming them. Often, i'll give an answer and then remove the last 1/3, and then it seems just right
